<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section" style="background:var(--color-iron-50);border-top:1px solid var(--color-iron-100)">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <div class="kicker">Common questions</div>
    <h2 class="h1 mt-2 mb-6">What homeowners ask before booking.</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details open>
        <summary><span>How long does an Ironside floor take to install?</span><span class="chev">+</span></summary>
        <div class="a"><p>One day for a standard 2-car garage. Grinding starts at 8am, final topcoat lays down around 3pm, walkable by 6pm, parkable the next morning. For 3-car garages or heavy prep, we schedule one and a half days.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary><span>Is polyaspartic really better than epoxy?</span><span class="chev">+</span></summary>
        <div class="a"><p>For cure speed, UV stability, and hot-tire resistance, yes. For raw chemical resistance, it's a wash. We install both &mdash; we'll recommend epoxy when it's the right call.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary><span>What does "lifetime warranty" actually cover?</span><span class="chev">+</span></summary>
        <div class="a"><p>The coating system itself &mdash; adhesion, delamination, hot-tire pickup, UV yellowing. Transferable one time to a subsequent homeowner. Full written document handed over at project close.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary><span>Do you acid-etch?</span><span class="chev">+</span></summary>
        <div class="a"><p>No. Acid weakens the top layer of concrete and traps moisture vapor under the coating. Every floor we install is diamond-ground to CSP-2 or CSP-3.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary><span>Do you service my city?</span><span class="chev">+</span></summary>
        <div class="a"><p>We're Oakville-based and service Burlington, Milton, Hamilton, Ancaster, Stoney Creek, and West Mississauga. Outside this radius we'll refer you to a vetted partner.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary><span>Can I see samples before I commit?</span><span class="chev">+</span></summary>
        <div class="a"><p>Yes &mdash; every in-home consult includes a physical sample kit with the 8 most-requested flake blends. You pick the floor with your actual lighting and cabinetry in view.</p></div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

